        "client_msg_id": "c9788015-57e9-414c-a46c-c9fa68680d95",
        "text": "I don't think the \"blast radius\" of a crash is orthogonal. On the contrary, it's why larger assemblies cannot afford the crash-only approach. Complex state takes too much time to rebuild. And it takes an even larger embedding system to handle the reboot. Once you reach the scale where a system is one of a very few, crashing is no longer an option.",
